        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 20 at 5:07PM CDT by NWS Birmingham AL</headline>
        <description>At 507 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Coaling, or 7 miles southeast of Tuscaloosa, moving north at 5 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Southeastern Tuscaloosa, Coaling, McFarland Mall, Duncanville,
Cottondale, Camp Horne B.S.A., Hagler, and Taylorville.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
